snippet.textDisplay:
People who are in college and around that typical age group buy into the humorous idea that they should be like that.

As a former college student who worked multiple jobs, I bought the bare necessities and got creative. It’s not that hard. I’m saying this for those that need this: quit being lazy and thinking that’s all there is to life when it comes to college.

It maybe seem like I’m a negative Nancy but a lot of these habits carry for life and lead to a crap ton of health issues.

Yes, this is something I am passionate about I guess p

snippet.textDisplay:
Oke for ramen,
i use chicken breasts that i bake in my airfryer for about 15 min at 200c° if i have the time marinated with soy and ketjap.

And for toppings i add anything from:
Frozen pees i put in the boil water the last 30 sec.
Frozen beans put in for 1 min.
Bean sprouts boiled for 30.sec.
Carrots, thinly sliced
Bell peppers, thinly sliced
Mushrooms, chestnuts, white, whatever you have.
Boiled egg like Joshua did, or trow in an egg with the noodles, like without the shell, stirr the noodles for tiny peices of egg and ooff more deliciousness.

Aditional toppins,
Fried onions
Peanuts, cashews
Toasted sesame seeds
Chives
Green onion sliced
Thinly sliced garlic
A few strips.of nori


Add any of these and your noodles will be amazing..you dont even need the proteins like chicken or pork cause those are expensive. Just have some pees and beans in the freezer and jazz up those noods

snippet.textDisplay:
My go to college meal was onigiri.
Rice, rice vinegar, a little sugar, sriracha mayo, canned tuna, nori. Make a whole bunch, keeps nice, easy to grab out of the fridge and just GO.
It would be like $1 each if you got name brand ingredients, more like $0.70 each if you get store brand. Super cheap, and pretty damn filling. 3 is a good whole meal, and you won’t feel hungry again for hours. Only down side is it takes a little practice to make them just right, and it’s a little time consuming to form all of them. Good for a Saturday night with the boys though.
